.:: Puzzle 2x6-Level-1-3::.
The people use 6 different means of transport: ship, boat, bike, motorbike, jet-ski, airplane
The people have 6 different jobs:  social-worker, electrician, coach, librarian, bartender, accountant
1. the person driving the jet-ski is on the right of the person driving the airplane##1
2. the librarian is on the right of the person driving the ship##1
3. the person driving the airplane is on the right of the person driving the motorbike##1
4. the person driving the bike is on the right of the bartender##1
5. the person driving the jet-ski is on the right of the accountant##1
6. the person driving the jet-ski is on the left of the electrician##1
7. the librarian is on the far right##1
8. the coach is the person driving the motorbike##1
9. the person driving the bike is the librarian##1

.:: Answer ::.
|               |    1    |   2    |     3     |     4     |   5    |     6     |
| Transport   | motorbike   | airplane   | jet-ski      | boat | ship  | bike   |
| Job   | coach | accountant | social-worker | electrician   | bartender | librarian |

